8 SECTION 3. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
9 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 812 of Title 17, unless there is
10 created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
11 A. The Corporation Commission is directed and authorized to
12 promulgate rules governing the operations for energy facilities for
13 the purpose of protecting the interests and property of the citizens
14 of this state.
15 B. Any facility operator desiring to commence any energy
16 facility in this state shall, prior to commencing any such activity:
17 1. Be duly registered with or under the jurisdiction of the
18 Commission;
19 2. Provide a form of financial security which meets the
20 provisions of Section 160.15 of Title 17 of the Oklahoma Statutes,
21 if applicable, or provide a form of financial security, in the form
22 and amount to be determined by the Commission, as applicable, which
23 shall remain in effect until release is authorized by the
24 Commission; and
